<doc>
  <member name="ERole">
    <summary>
      <para>The <b>ERole</b> enumeration defines constants that indicate the role that the system has assigned to an audio endpoint device.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>The <see cref="IMMDeviceEnumerator.GetDefaultAudioEndpoint" /> and <see cref="IMMNotificationClient.OnDefaultDeviceChanged" /> methods use the constants defined in the <b>ERole</b> enumeration.</para>
      <para>For more information, see <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/CoreAudio/device-roles">Device Roles</a>.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/CoreAudio/core-audio-enumerations">Core Audio Enumerations</seealso>
    <seealso cref="IMMDeviceEnumerator.GetDefaultAudioEndpoint" />
    <seealso cref="IMMNotificationClient.OnDefaultDeviceChanged" />
  </member>
  <member name="ERole.eConsole">
    <summary>
      <para>Games, system notification sounds, and voice commands.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="ERole.eMultimedia">
    <summary>
      <para>Music, movies, narration, and live music recording.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="ERole.eCommunications">
    <summary>
      <para>Voice communications (talking to another person).</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="ERole.ERole_enum_count">
    <summary>
      <para>The number of members in the <see cref="ERole" /> enumeration (not counting the ERole_enum_count member).</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>